{"type":"message","id":"75b878cf","parentId":"45a76fa5","timestamp":"2026-03-19T07:54:33.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"找到了！让我读取这个skill的配置。","thinkingSignature":"220d93087e612b836ba0b32af5dc007036d52c6de49c0da76b6023f3ea0c85bd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_va85awr21ye8_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\news-summary\\SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":6567,"output":53,"cacheRead":36688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43308,"cost":{"input":0.0019701,"output":0.0000636,"cacheRead":0.00110064,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0031343399999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773906870688}}
{"type":"message","id":"a10e6f15","parentId":"75b878cf","timestamp":"2026-03-19T07:54:33.006Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_va85awr21ye8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: news-summary\ndescription: This skill should be used when the user asks for news updates, daily briefings, or what's happening in the world. Fetches news from Chinese news websites and can create voice summaries.\n---\n\n# News Summary (国内版)\n\n## Overview\n\n获取并总结国内可访问的新闻源。\n\n## News Sources\n\n### 今日头条 (Primary)\n```bash\n# 热点新闻 API\ncurl -s \"https://www.toutiao.com/api/pc/feed/?category=news_hot&utm_source=toutiao&widen=1&max_behot_time=0&max_behot_time_tmp=0&tadrequire=true&as=A1152B8F0C9E0F8&cp=595F8C0E2A0E1\"\n```\n\n### 网易新闻\n```bash\n# 排行榜\ncurl -s \"https://news.163.com/special/cm_yaowen20200213/\"\n```\n\n### 新浪新闻\n```bash\n# 国内新闻\ncurl -s \"https://news.sina.cn/?vt=1&ws=1\"\n```\n\n### 腾讯新闻\n```bash\n# 要闻\ncurl -s \"https://news.qq.com/\"\n```\n\n## Parse News\n\n使用 PowerShell 解析网页示例：\n```powershell\n$html = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"https://news.sina.cn/\" -UseBasicParsing\n$html.ParsedHtml.getElementsByTagName(\"a\") | Select-Object -First 20 innerText, href\n```\n\n## Workflow\n\n### Text summary\n1. 获取今日头条热点新闻\n2. 补充其他源（网易/腾讯）\n3. 整理关键信息\n4. 按分类展示\n\n### Voice summary\n1. 创建文字摘要\n2. 用 OpenAI TTS 生成语音\n3. 发送语音消息\n\n## Output Format\n\n```\n📰 新闻摘要 [日期]\n\n🔴 热点\n- 新闻标题1\n- 新闻标题2\n\n📌 国内\n- 新闻标题\n\n🌍 国际\n- 新闻标题\n\n💰 财经\n- 新闻标题\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- 保持简洁，6-10条重点新闻\n- 优先最新和热点新闻\n- 语音版控制在2分钟内\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773906873004}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef521a66","parentId":"a10e6f15","timestamp":"2026-03-19T07:54:41.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"这个文件没有提到 cron schedule。让我查看一下 cron 相关的配置文件或 skill 看看有没有配置新闻推送的时间。","thinkingSignature":"13ea5dfbb50d188b8ff6c603b11f97856c7f1ba17ab0274757bd0188466b3a01"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tho4bxlosln2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\*\\*.md -Pattern \"cron|schedule|推送\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":7103,"output":95,"cacheRead":36688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43886,"cost":{"input":0.0021309,"output":0.00011399999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00110064,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0033455399999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773906873006}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbdf03f2","parentId":"ef521a66","timestamp":"2026-03-19T07:54:46.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tho4bxlosln2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"skills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:2:name: cron-mastery\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:3:description: Master OpenClaw's timing systems. Use for scheduling reliable reminders, se\r\ntting up periodic maintenance (janitor jobs), and understanding when to use Cron vs Heartbeat for time-sensitive tasks.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:6:# Cron Mastery\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:8:**Rule #1: Heartbeats drift. Cron is precise.**\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:10:This skill provides the definitive guide for managing time in OpenClaw 2026.2.15+. It s\r\nolves the \"I missed my reminder\" problem by enforcing a strict separation between casual checks (heartbeat) and hard sc\r\nhedules (cron).\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:17:| **Cron** | \"I will run at exactly X time\" | Reminders (\"in 5 mins\"), daily reports, s\r\nystem maintenance. | **Clutter:** Creates one-off jobs that need cleanup. |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:21:**Rule:** Never use `act:wait` or internal loops for long delays (>1 min). Use `cron:ad\r\nd` with a one-shot `at` schedule.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:23:### Precision & The \"Scheduler Tick\"\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:24:While Cron is precise, execution depends on the **Gateway Heartbeat** (typically every \r\n10-60s). A job set for `:00` seconds will fire on the first \"tick\" after that time. Expect up to ~30s of variance depen\r\nding on your gateway config.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:43:  \"schedule\": { \"kind\": \"at\", \"at\": \"2026-02-06T01:30:00Z\" },\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:57:  \"schedule\": { \"kind\": \"every\", \"everyMs\": 3600000 },\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:66:### Cron Concurrency Rule (Stabilized)\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:67:Pre-2026.2.15, the \"Add-then-Update\" pattern caused deadlocks. While this is now stabil\r\nized, it is still **best practice** to pass all parameters (including `wakeMode: \"now\"`) directly in the initial `cron.\r\nadd` call for maximum efficiency.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:71:**Note:** As of v2026.2.14, OpenClaw includes **maintenance recompute semantics**. The \r\ngateway now automatically cleans up stuck jobs and repairs corrupted schedules. \r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:78:Sub-agents (`isolated`) often have restricted tool policies and cannot call `gateway` o\r\nr delete other `cron` jobs. For system maintenance like the Janitor, **always** target the `main` session via `systemEv\r\nent` so the primary agent (with full tool access) performs the cleanup.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:82:For cron to work, the agent **must** know its time.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:90:**Solution:** If you need to \"wait\" across turns, you **MUST** schedule a Cron job.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:93:*   **Wait > 1 minute (async):** Use Cron with `wakeMode: \"now\"`.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:97:If you have old cron jobs using these patterns, update them:\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:101:| `\"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"at\", \"atMs\": 1234567890}` | `\"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"at\", \"at\":\r\n \"2026-02-06T01:30:00Z\"}` |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:105:| `cron.update` after `cron.add` | Single-step `cron.add` with all properties |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:109:*   **\"My reminder didn't fire\":** Check `cron:list`. Verify the `at` timestamp is in \r\nthe future (ISO 8601 format). Ensure `wakeMode: \"now\"` is set.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:110:*   **\"Gateway Timeout (10000ms)\":** This happens if the `cron` tool takes too long (h\r\nuge job list or file lock). \r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:111:    - **Fix 1:** Manually delete `~/.openclaw/state/cron/jobs.json` and restart the ga\r\nteway if it's corrupted.\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:95:### 3. ����Crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:168:### Crontab���ã�����������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:193:# ����crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:194:crontab -e\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:257:# �������Զ�����������crontab�У�\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:9:- **Cron�����޸�**����������PATH/HOME������v2.2.1��\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:91:- **v2.2.1** (2026-03-06)���޸�cron�����������⣨����PATH/HOME��?????\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:100:- ��ʱ����`crontab -l | grep seamless`\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:5:### ?? �����޸���Cron������������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:8:- **֢״**����ؽű���cron�����г���ʧ�ܣ�09:00-10:00��\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:9:- **����ԭ��**��cron����ȱ��PATH���ã��Ҳ���openclaw����\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:21:cron��ʱ���� �� ȱ��PATH�������� �� �Ҳ���openclaw���� �� \r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-REPORT-v2.2.3.md:87:## ?? ����Crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:138:# ���ӵ�crontab��ÿ10���Ӽ�飩\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:236:- ʹ��cron tool��agentTurn\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:251:- ? **Cron�����޸�**����������PATH/HOME��������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:303:2. ��鶨ʱ����`crontab -l | grep seamless`\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:322:- v2.2.1��Cron�����޸�������������?????\r\nskills\\proactivity\\boundaries.md:22:| ASK | Needs approval first | send, buy, delete, reschedule, notify |\r\nskills\\proactivity\\execution.md:27:- Use for external communication, commitments, spending, deletion, and schedule chan\r\nges\r\nskills\\proactivity\\setup.md:98:- For send, spend, delete, reschedule, or contact actions, stop and ask first\r\nskills\\self-improving\\boundaries.md:22:| Schedules | General patterns OK (\"busy mornings\"), not specific times |\r\nskills\\self-improving\\operations.md:47:### Weekly Maintenance (Cron)\r\nskills\\self-improving\\scaling.md:75:Next scheduled: 2026-03-01"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5578,"aggregated":"skills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:2:name: cron-mastery\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:3:description: Master OpenClaw's timing systems. Use for scheduling reliable reminders, se\r\ntting up periodic maintenance (janitor jobs), and understanding when to use Cron vs Heartbeat for time-sensitive tasks.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:6:# Cron Mastery\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:8:**Rule #1: Heartbeats drift. Cron is precise.**\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:10:This skill provides the definitive guide for managing time in OpenClaw 2026.2.15+. It s\r\nolves the \"I missed my reminder\" problem by enforcing a strict separation between casual checks (heartbeat) and hard sc\r\nhedules (cron).\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:17:| **Cron** | \"I will run at exactly X time\" | Reminders (\"in 5 mins\"), daily reports, s\r\nystem maintenance. | **Clutter:** Creates one-off jobs that need cleanup. |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:21:**Rule:** Never use `act:wait` or internal loops for long delays (>1 min). Use `cron:ad\r\nd` with a one-shot `at` schedule.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:23:### Precision & The \"Scheduler Tick\"\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:24:While Cron is precise, execution depends on the **Gateway Heartbeat** (typically every \r\n10-60s). A job set for `:00` seconds will fire on the first \"tick\" after that time. Expect up to ~30s of variance depen\r\nding on your gateway config.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:43:  \"schedule\": { \"kind\": \"at\", \"at\": \"2026-02-06T01:30:00Z\" },\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:57:  \"schedule\": { \"kind\": \"every\", \"everyMs\": 3600000 },\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:66:### Cron Concurrency Rule (Stabilized)\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:67:Pre-2026.2.15, the \"Add-then-Update\" pattern caused deadlocks. While this is now stabil\r\nized, it is still **best practice** to pass all parameters (including `wakeMode: \"now\"`) directly in the initial `cron.\r\nadd` call for maximum efficiency.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:71:**Note:** As of v2026.2.14, OpenClaw includes **maintenance recompute semantics**. The \r\ngateway now automatically cleans up stuck jobs and repairs corrupted schedules. \r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:78:Sub-agents (`isolated`) often have restricted tool policies and cannot call `gateway` o\r\nr delete other `cron` jobs. For system maintenance like the Janitor, **always** target the `main` session via `systemEv\r\nent` so the primary agent (with full tool access) performs the cleanup.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:82:For cron to work, the agent **must** know its time.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:90:**Solution:** If you need to \"wait\" across turns, you **MUST** schedule a Cron job.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:93:*   **Wait > 1 minute (async):** Use Cron with `wakeMode: \"now\"`.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:97:If you have old cron jobs using these patterns, update them:\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:101:| `\"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"at\", \"atMs\": 1234567890}` | `\"schedule\": {\"kind\": \"at\", \"at\":\r\n \"2026-02-06T01:30:00Z\"}` |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:105:| `cron.update` after `cron.add` | Single-step `cron.add` with all properties |\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:109:*   **\"My reminder didn't fire\":** Check `cron:list`. Verify the `at` timestamp is in \r\nthe future (ISO 8601 format). Ensure `wakeMode: \"now\"` is set.\r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:110:*   **\"Gateway Timeout (10000ms)\":** This happens if the `cron` tool takes too long (h\r\nuge job list or file lock). \r\nskills\\cron-mastery\\SKILL.md:111:    - **Fix 1:** Manually delete `~/.openclaw/state/cron/jobs.json` and restart the ga\r\nteway if it's corrupted.\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:95:### 3. ����Crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:168:### Crontab���ã�����������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:193:# ����crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:194:crontab -e\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\ERROR-HANDLING-GUIDE.md:257:# �������Զ�����������crontab�У�\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:9:- **Cron�����޸�**����������PATH/HOME������v2.2.1��\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:91:- **v2.2.1** (2026-03-06)���޸�cron�����������⣨����PATH/HOME��?????\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\README.md:100:- ��ʱ����`crontab -l | grep seamless`\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:5:### ?? �����޸���Cron������������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:8:- **֢״**����ؽű���cron�����г���ʧ�ܣ�09:00-10:00��\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:9:- **����ԭ��**��cron����ȱ��PATH���ã��Ҳ���openclaw����\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-NOTES.md:21:cron��ʱ���� �� ȱ��PATH�������� �� �Ҳ���openclaw���� �� \r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\RELEASE-REPORT-v2.2.3.md:87:## ?? ����Crontab\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:138:# ���ӵ�crontab��ÿ10���Ӽ�飩\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:236:- ʹ��cron tool��agentTurn\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:251:- ? **Cron�����޸�**����������PATH/HOME��������\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:303:2. ��鶨ʱ����`crontab -l | grep seamless`\r\nskills\\miliger-context-manager\\SKILL.md:322:- v2.2.1��Cron�����޸�������������?????\r\nskills\\proactivity\\boundaries.md:22:| ASK | Needs approval first | send, buy, delete, reschedule, notify |\r\nskills\\proactivity\\execution.md:27:- Use for external communication, commitments, spending, deletion, and schedule chan\r\nges\r\nskills\\proactivity\\setup.md:98:- For send, spend, delete, reschedule, or contact actions, stop and ask first\r\nskills\\self-improving\\boundaries.md:22:| Schedules | General patterns OK (\"busy mornings\"), not specific times |\r\nskills\\self-improving\\operations.md:47:### Weekly Maintenance (Cron)\r\nskills\\self-improving\\scaling.md:75:Next scheduled: 2026-03-01","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773906886623}}
